# CreateNewEpic Implementation-First Guidance

The required `.agents/epic.md` output is a sanctioned LoopRelay operational artifact. Creating it is part of the roadmap loop, not auxiliary documentation.

Preserve the strategic epic authoring that this prompt requires: repository grounding, explicit assumptions, dependencies, constraints, risks, acceptance criteria, and milestone roadmap content all belong in `.agents/epic.md`.

Keep the implementation-first boundary clear. The epic should define capability outcomes, constraints, dependency signals, validation expectations, and milestone-level strategic progress. It must not become an implementation task list, file-level plan, code-change prescription, execution prompt, separate design document, or repository inventory.
